Sentencas: La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3 (LSCM) has been applied as hydrogen electrode (cathode) material in solid oxide electrolysis cells operating with different steam concentrations (20, 40, 60 and 80 vol.% absolute humidity (AH)) using 40 sccm H-2 carrier gas at 800, 850 and 900 degrees C, respectively.
Titulo: La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3 as hydrogen electrode for solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: Impedance spectra and voltage-current curves were measured as a function of cell electrolysis current density and steam concentration to characterize the cell performance.
Titulo: La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3 as hydrogen electrode for solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: The cell resistance decreased with the increase in electrolysis current density while increased with the increase in steam concentration under the same electrolysis current density.
Titulo: La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3 as hydrogen electrode for solid oxide electrolysis cells

Sentencas: At 1.6 V applied electrolysis voltage, the maximum consumed current density increased from 431 mA cm(-2) for 20 vol.% AH to 593 mA cm(-2) for 80 vol.% AH at 850 degrees C. Polarization and impedance spectra experiments revealed that LSCM-YSZ hydrogen electrode played a major role in the electrolysis reaction.
Titulo: La0.75Sr0.25Cr0.5Mn0.5O3 as hydrogen electrode for solid oxide electrolysis cells
